ABUJA – The Progressives Governors Forum PGF rose from their crucial meeting Sunday night in Abuja declaring that the February date proposed for the party’s convention remains Sacrosanct. The Chairman of the PGF and Governor of Kebbi State disclosed after the meeting that nothing has changed to necessitate an alteration in the timeline agreed upon after consultation with President Mohammadu Buhari. He however insisted that the actual date of the Convention is that of the party to announce, saying that the party will make that disclosure soonest. CONVENTION: APC Chieftains Sue Buni, Want Exercise Stopped Private: APC Convention: New Group Emerges, Urges Tinubu, Buni… Details later